# Architecture (strict)

## Standard UI library (read-only)

- **Do not modify** any files under **`src/components/ui/`** or **`src/components/ai-elements/`**. Treat them as a fixed standard library (shadcn + ai-elements), same as vendor code.
- **Customize only outside those folders:** compose in `src/features/...`, thin wrapper components, `className` / props from parents, theme tokens in global styles‚Äînot edits inside `ui` or `ai-elements`.

## Feature ownership

- **All product/feature logic lives under `src/features/<feature-name>/`** (hooks, components, utils, types, constants specific to that feature).
- **`src/app/`** stays thin: routing, layouts, and wiring that imports from `src/features` (or shared libs). Do not grow heavy UI or business logic in route files‚Äîextract to a feature.
- **Shared cross-feature code** goes in `src/lib/`, `src/hooks/` (only if truly shared), or small shared modules‚Äînot inside a single feature folder unless it is feature-private.

## Colocation

- Keep **components and their local utils** under the same feature tree (e.g. `src/features/chat/components/...` next to `src/features/chat/utils/...`).
- **Types are not inlined** ‚Äî they live only in dedicated type files (see Types below), still under that feature, or in `src/global.types.ts` when shared across features.
- Avoid a flat dump of unrelated files at the feature root; group by subfolder or by slice (e.g. `components/`, `hooks/`, `utils/`, `types/`).

## Types (strict)

- **Never define feature or domain types inside `.tsx` or implementation `.ts` files** (components, hooks, utils). No `interface`/`type` blocks for shared props, models, or API shapes next to implementation‚Äîextract them.
- **Use dedicated files only:** `types.ts`, `*.types.ts`, or a `types/` folder within the feature (e.g. `src/features/chat/types/message.types.ts`).
- **Shared types** (used by more than one feature): **`src/global.types.ts` only**‚Äîone canonical file for app-wide types. Do not scatter the same shared shapes across `lib` or feature files; add or extend exports there and import with `from "@/global.types"`.

## TypeScript and lint discipline (strict)

- **Minimize casting and assertions.** Avoid `as ‚Ä¶`, `as unknown as ‚Ä¶`, and non-null `!` to force types. Prefer narrowing (e.g. `typeof`, `in`, discriminated unions), type guards, well-typed generics, and validated boundaries. Literal `as const` for readonly tuples/literals is fine when it improves inference‚Äîdo not use it to paper over unsafe `any`.
- **No suppressions in source.** Do not add `eslint-disable` (line, block, or file), `eslint-disable-next-line`, `@ts-ignore`, `@ts-expect-error`, or `@ts-nocheck`. If a rule or error is wrong, fix the code or adjust **project** ESLint/TS config‚Äînot inline directives in app or feature files.

## Single responsibility and file size

- **One main concern per file.** Split large components into smaller presentational pieces and hooks; extract pure helpers to `utils` (or `*.utils.ts`) in the same feature.
- **Prefer several small files over one ‚Äúgod‚Äù file.** If a file mixes unrelated UI, data fetching, and formatting, split it.
- **Reuse deliberately:** import from `src/components/ui` and `src/components/ai-elements` (read-only); do not copy-paste their internals into features or edit those directories.

## SOLID (practical)

- **S** ‚Äî Each module does one job (UI vs data vs formatting).
- **O** ‚Äî Extend via composition/props/hooks rather than editing unrelated modules for every change.
- **L** ‚Äî Substitute implementations via clear props/contracts (e.g. same interface for alternate renderers).
- **I** ‚Äî Small, focused props and hook return shapes; avoid ‚Äúmega props‚Äù objects.
- **D** ‚Äî Features depend on abstractions (`lib` APIs, hooks) rather than reaching deep into other features‚Äô internals; import concrete modules by path (no barrel-only `index.ts` re-exports‚Äîsee project rule **no-barrel-index**).

## Example layout

```text
src/
  global.types.ts   # shared types across features only
  features/chat/
    components/
    hooks/
    utils/
    types/          # or types.ts / *.types.ts ‚Äî feature-only; never inside component files
```
